review: Great service! Enjoyed a fun night out! Our waitress was awesome and very attentive. She checked on us often and was very friendly.  I did the $15 endless appetizer option since I could decide what to get and was in the mood for small plates. I had the BBQ flatbread, the pot stickers, the loaded potato skins, and the chicken quesadilla.  The BBQ flatbread and the pot stickers were really good and flavorful! The loaded potato skins were just okay. The chicken quesadilla was also really good and had a lot of flavor!  Perfect deal for someone who is indecisive about what they want!

Grab 2 special for $15 was a good deal.  I got two half racks of ribs, plus onion rings and mac n cheese.  Ribs were tasty, but I've had more succulent.  Onion rings were very good. My wife had the french dip sandwich, which had an odd after taste.  She loved the fries, though.  Soft drinks and iced tea were good. Server was friendly and quick.  We sat in the side dining room facing the parking lot, which has big bright windows.

Friday's is a good place to goto for a good lunch or dinner all of the meals that have the JD sauce are very good this stuff would even make anchovies taste good. I wish they had one in Calvert county going to Waldorf (not an area that is really safe anymore) or annapolis for dinner is a long drive.

The service was too slow during happy hour on a Wednesday which shouldn't be. Our server sucked. I've eaten/worked at many restaurants and this is by far the worst one. I've eaten at the Dover DE location and the service there was better. My last time coming here.
Friday's in Annapolis is great. Food and staff is awesome. Lots of choices on the menu for both adults and kids.
Great food . Wonderful server Sasha . Thank you for helping celebrate my daughters birthday .

This Fridays is good! I love Fridays! They have the best all day happy hour on top of their daily specials for happy hour. Friday's is like Denny's, you have to find a good one and stick to it.  Fridays to avoid- Towson Town Center - SUPER Slow, under-staffed, and they don't care. Fridays to attend- White Marsh OR Columbia- always phenomenal service Oh and now Annapolis! Thanks!

Our waiter Sasha was very good. Alway attentive and very nice. We got the endless apps though I should have just ordered mine off the regular app menu since the amount I got was the same. I paid $12 for something I could have gotten for $9. Not their fault though. The potstickers are always good and so are the wings.
Slow service unfortunately was the downfall. 3 out 4 meals showed up first. Our 4th meal showed up around 7 minutes later. Not a lot of teamwork. Not a manager in sight.

My waiter was amazing !! Attentive and very quick! His recommendations were awesome and everyone he had all of his tables in a good mood! Food was good, nice and hot! They have some great lunch deals. Be sure and check it out!

My friends and I went to this location for lunch. The parking lot was great since there was plenty space. The moment we entered the lobby, we were greeted and seated by a host immediately. That was great except it was awkward to see our blonde host with a collar unbuttoned black shirt with a silver necklace, as if we were in the gay nightclub. Our waiter was accommodating and very awesome! Wish I knew his name, but he was the one with awesome dreadlocks and I would like to have him as a chillin' friend and playing video games. He took our orders efficiency and there was no awkward conversation between us. I ordered the Memphis BBQ wings and Jack Daniel's Burger. Our food arrived in about 10 minutes and that's very impressive. My food was perfectly cooked except there was a bit too much grease on my burger. However I loved their Jack Daniel's sauce and I loved dipping my fries in it. When we were done with our meals, I'm very impressed with our waiter's timing skills. I was also impressed by the fact he tried to communicate with me in gestures since he asked me if I wanted dessert. He signed "thank you" perfectly. He is totally awesome and he has my respect. If it wasn't for him, I would give this restaurant a 4 star due to our host's poor dress code and too much grease in my burger.

No real changes here. Service was good. I did not see the cleanliness issues others noted. Burger was properly cooked (ordered medium rare). Very greasy. Service was okay and kitchen was slow. No one had a clue about the difference between malt vinegar and salad vinegar. Like today I'll stop in when I need to get something to eat but never for an enjoyable meal. Meh.

We have not been to Fridays in forever.... Went on a whim and had a great time... Tiana was very patient explaining the $10 menu and her service was fantastic... We will make Friday's more of a regular routine....

We came to TGI Fridays in Annapols. My daughter loved it. She suggested me to write a service review. Our server Sasha was great, sweet and kind. The food was very delicious. The restaurant atmosphere was very homey. I recommend coming here since this was our first time as well, but that just show how good the place is .

My family and I enjoy the menu, but the service leaves something to be desired at this location. Unlike most restaurants where you get 1 person waiting on you, here in the bar area you may get five or more. I know the theory, they are trying to overlap servers to try and keep someone stopping by frequently, but it is not working. You ask person A for something, they pass it to person B to do and person C shows up with a straw or napkin for you and says they never got the message, but fear not they will get it for you. Then 10 min. Later person D shows up with that ketchup you originally asked person A for. Problem is now your fries are ice cold or you already ate them because you got tired of waiting.    Ok, let me tell you about this Smoke Stack Burger I tried. Man it sounded so good with sausage squeezed between two patties... well, lol, i guess thats what I got. I pulled the patties apart to see two small pieces of meet that put me to mind of 2 small pieces of diced ham.  Overall it had a good taste though.

Bottom Line:  Highly processed, unhealthy bar food but an ok place to get a drink before or after a movie. Ever since Office Space I find my disappointed that the T.G.I. Fridays staff no longer wear pieces of flair.  I also find T.G.I. Fridays, a chain restaurant with bar food, to be irrelevant in Annapolis because there are so many better choices. For me, the only purpose of this Fridays is either a cocktail before a menu or a night cap thereafter since this is the only place in Annapolis Harbour Center that serves alcohol.  If I'm drunk enough, some of the appetizers may seem appealing.  What I do like about Fridays is they do have a handful of items that are always considered to be on happy hour.  Service here is fine.

The food here is absolutely incredible. We came here with low expectations after our other plans fell through, and couldn't be more happy that they did.  Our server Eileen was amazing, and helped us when we had trouble swiping one of our cards. She even asked us about customizing our order exactly how we wanted. Very friendly, and very hard working. Everyone here is.  Our food came out fast, and and fresh.  Would definitely recommend to anyone looking for a. Great meal, that comes out fast in huge portions!
Three servers...over one hour...no silverware...we got our own napkins...had to repeatedly ask for food...excuses and mass confusion. This place gets worse by the day.

If I am honest, nothing too too special. My husband and I came here for a round of endless appetizers (really the only reason to come here in my opinion). It took forever for our first round to come out, but it did improve after that. The Memphis BBQ wings are probably the best thing on that menu. The potstickers were also pretty tasty. Our waitress was just so-so. Didn't make an extra effort, but I don't have too much to complain about. Probably won't come back unless for endless apps because there are just too many better options around here.

Tgif annapolis is a great place to eat quickly, and get good food. Our server Kirby was excellent, and very personable. Fried string beans always excellent. My burger and wifes mahi mahi sandwich were large and good. Love their fries too. Get the TGIF app for free appetizer.

One of the worst experiences I have had at a restaurant recently.  Got there and everything was good, but then the entire complex had a power outage, fine not their problem.  Then they started rushing people to pay and leave since they couldnt have people in the store without power. One guy at the bar had just ordered a drink and they kept telling him you have to finish it immediately or leave.  When he asked them if he could just leave and not pay for it the manager told him he had drank too much of it, so she wouldn't comp the drink.   I tried paying with cash, they said they couldnt give change and I would have to pay with credit card.  Finally they took a copy of the credit card because there was no power and after I left I realized that not only did they not discount us for not being able to finish our food, but they actually over charged us and I had to go back and complain
Decent. We miss the fried mac and cheese nuggets. My French dip was pretty good with the right amount of horseradish. Chicken fingers were meh. Salad was meh. Good service.

Men's bathroom is disgusting like Penn Station NYC at 4am. Waitress said there is an "all girl" staff, so they don't check cleanliness regularly. With that in mind, I'd hate to visit the kitchen. - From, Lost Customer

Oh man, I'm late on this one! This is from Veteran's Day 2011! :P Friday's was offering a special for veterans, and as my dad is a vet, we decided to partake. We got in RIGHT before the lunch rush, and ordered.  Dad had the hibachi chicken skewers and I had the Jack Daniels flat iron steak.  For the record, the flat iron steak is my go to meal at Fridays. You just can't go wrong with it!  Dad said he liked his skewers too. Servers were friendly and attentive, and our bill was immediately corrected when the vet's day special hadn't been put on the bill the first time. I've never been unhappy with Fridays, and will continue to patronize them.

What can you expect? it's a TGI fridays..... Solid food, friendly service, big portions, if you're not very hungry I wouldn't suggest eating here. The two happy hours are nice, especially the one from 10 til close. they offer 4 dollar long island ice teas during this happy hour. Now, this is the only complaint I have... my long island tasted like straight sour mix with no liquor and it was pretty obvious our bartender did not know how to properly make this drink. But they were only four dollars so I had about 5 or 6 and caught a nice buzz. That's the only reason this review gets an extra star.

2.5 star experience when I dined today. Suprisingly, this TGI Fridays usually is on point so today was an off day. Two issues today. First was they advertised on their board by the front door a Sunday special....half price appetizers. Awesome! I've gotten this special before at my table and it really is a great deal. Sadly, it seems they changed this special to a "bar area only" special. Except they advertised it in a non-bar area and did not mention anywhere on the board the special had limited seating areas in which this would be honored. So my table couldn't partake. I expressed my disappointment that my table was excluded but the table that was making eye contact with me an arm lengths away could, but to no avail. My waiter said we could move to the bar area, but that would require my party getting back in line to be seated. Really? And stand with our bar drinks (since they have no problem spreading THOSE bar items to any table in the building...did that sound snarky? Eh, I stand by it.) No, thank you. While my table remained friendly the entire time, I feel the waiter assumed we were going to be difficult and just found other places to be for most of our meal. So service was a negative today. Again, usually I have good experiences with the staff here.  Just an FYI that has nothing to do with my rating. The 2 for $12/$16 options have changed to a massacred, wimpy version of its former self. Gone are most of the good choices that made you go "wow, that's a great deal" or even "wow, so many good sounding options." Now, you'll probably check out the full, higher priced menu more carefully. That's not bad in itself, but may have Friday's lose some of the bang for your buck it had going for it. So 2.5 today and prior experiences being 4 stars, comes to a (possibly too low) 3 stars. I'll be back, but I may have to play 21 questions with the host to guarantee I am in a seat that has all of the options Friday's has to offer available to me.

It's Fridays.  What more could you want? We went here Saturday and the food was amazing as always.  I had a black angus burger, fried mozzarella, and a piece of chocolate peanut butter pie all for $12.99.  You can't beat that.  Our waiter, Steve, was super awesome.

Why is it always so dead in here? Thank goodness Friday's now has 2 happy hours. the 2nd being from 10? to close. We got here around 11pm on a Saturday night. As usual, the service was a little slow. But, for what I went for, I was happy. Wings and beer. That's all I wanted. That's all I ordered. That's all I need to live. The End.

The kids and I stopped in for a quick Saturday evening dinner and were not disappointed. It was beginning to get that after 5 weekend wait, but we were seated really quickly. Our waitress was fairly new, but very helpful. Our food was good and enjoyed by all. I have no complaints. I would go back.

Average at best. The waitress had a nasty attitude at first and that ticked us off, but she actually smiled halfway through the service so I guess that was better than nothing. I got the Jack Daniel's sirloin and shrimp and there was no shrimp on my plate so I had to give it back which was pretty annoying. I can say that the BBQ chicken flatbread was good but I was disappointed with the size of my sirloin and the small lump of french fries and one small piece of broccoli for my sides. If you have a good time at this place, it will be because of good conversation, not the food.

I has been a long time since I've been to a T.G.I.Friday's.  There's not much really specific to say about this particular Friday's.  It's cookie cutter by design. However...   My friend and I have been using coupons to extend our budget a bit.  We had a $5 off coupon to T.G.I.Friday's and I had heard they had a new menu, so we tried it.  Wow!  Lot's of budget friendly, waistline friendly, taste-bud friendly choices.  I am a big fan of the Parmesan-Crusted Chicken!   The chicken was just crispy enough, but not over done.  The tortellini was a nice pairing.  The tomato and mozzarella side was a nice change.  Can't wait to go back!
Server had several tables but did a phenomenal job! New "Whiskey Cake" is a real keeper. The California Club is very good sandwich actually my favorite on the menu. The bread is soft and warm.

Incredibly average. I'm beginning to dislike this chain as my experiences across a range of sites are consistently blah.  Mediocre food, distracted, poorly trained service is disappointing from a restaurant I've been coming to for over 20 years. Only bright spot was the naan-which.  I actually liked the dish.

I actually really like this Fridays. The service has always been consistently good and quick. There rarely is a wait for a table, or else there are bar tables open for open seating.  The mixed drinks have on occasion been subpar, but no complaints about the food or service. The bartenders just sometimes don't know what they are doing. No biggie- just order a beer or a glass of wine.

Waited 30 mins at a table in the bar area and was not once acknowledged yet the servers took care of there other tables. Was not a busy night, 4 tables in the bar area being used with 2 different servers   Was going for that apps but will not be coming back

On this occasion i had the Balsamic Chicken Ceasar Salad.  i enjoyed ths entree. I have ordered it before at another TGI Friday's and will order it again.  As usual we had to wait for seating, but no more than 10-15 minutes. Our waitress was pleasant and knowledgable.  Overall a good experence.
This is by far the best meal i have a had in a long time. I ordered the steak and mac and cheese and it was delicious. I recommend this place to anyone who wants a good meal.

Cool place to hang out for Happy Hour or a late night drink. The food not so much...Stopped in last Sat. night because they were the only restaurant open past 11pm besides the usual fast food joints. Sat at the bar and ordered something called shrimp and chicken pasta with cream sauce. I looked at it when the foodrunner dropped it off and thought it was a soup. Pasta was drowning in sauce. I was starving so I gave it a try and it was completely void of any taste. Funny thing is I told the bartender that I was not a fan of it and that I would like to order something else. He looked at me as though I had run over his puppy or something. "What's the problem?" he asked. I explained it to him and I got a nasty look. Ended up with the Ribeye Jack Daniels Steak and Shrimp. While certainly not the best steak I ever had, it got me full. Lesson learned! If I'm expecting quality food, go out early and avoid the overpriced, subpar food of TGI Fridays.

Going there is an abusive lesson in patience. 10 minutes before someone comes to the table, another 10 for drinks and they take up your plate when you still have food on it and don't ask if you're finished. Close and train for a month.
Don't come during the 12 dollars all you can eat. Service was terrible and wait staff clueless. Don't come go to Wendy's get better service
I came here for a quick glass of wine and was pleasantly surprised by the live music. Very nice evening.

Summing it up.. Food took a little bit longer than I expected, our server (who was great) must have been misinformed by the kitchen staff when we asked if we can do double string beans and wings but were told we can't. Lloyd (manager in charge) greeted us and took care of the problem, he was great and made it all better. I appreciate him and our server, Dawn.

I have to admit this is one of the better TGIFriday's I've  been in in awhile. The Missus and I came here to have lunch before a movie over at the Bowtie Cinema and it was actually pretty good. The service was friendly, attentive and quick. The food was served warm and it was actually pretty tasty. We also had a coupon which the waiter gratefully took and applied to our tab. The guy even kinda apologized for another customer who was being kind of rude an obnoxious. He seemed to take everything in stride. In fact, when we came back the next day (can you believe it?! Two days in a row.) he remembered us and asked if we wanted our "same table". I would have given this place five stars except that, let's face it, it's a Friday's.  Excellent experience over all.

I usually don't go to TGI Fridays, and this experience showed me why!  Let me start off by saying that I took my daughter here on our weekly Mommy-Daughter date night! This was a great location with great customer service!  However, the food was awful!  Now I remember why I never eat at Fridays!!

Really dirty. Our table had dried globs of bbq sauce and an old piece of bacon, the seat had lettuce on it, all of the menus had both dried and wet soda on them. There were French fries under our feet and my wife's fork had dried food on it. The bathrooms were dirty as well. They clearly don't clean this place. I'm glad I don't know what the kitchen looks like.

T.G.I.F.'s food will never be AMAZING but it's fast and convenient. Their bar service is the way to go since they are a little bit faster, plus they have all the good stuff behind them ;) I always order a Mojito or Watermelon Cooler: YUM.

First time here.  Friday night, 7:30, friendly staff, amazing appetizers (recommend pick 3).  Music is low, but present; TVs are available for sports fans, but not overwhelming; order comes up quick enough, and social feel is comfortable.  One of those places you feel good about going to.  Good food and drink selection.

Worst service especially when the bartender only had two tables! (Two tables and only two people at each table) The bartender got our order wrong then wanted to argue that boneless wings were not on the 474 menu... She never refilled our drinks... I had to ask another server for a refill! The other bartender came in with a dip in his mouth, with his hands grabbed it out, threw it away and then proceeded to touch the mixers and computer screen without washing his hands (I didn't see him wash his hands the entire time we were there). Our bartender kept talking to other coworkers and never came up to either table to see if we needed anything. The chicken tenders came out 35 minutes after we ordered them and the plate was so hot that it had to be in the window for a while ... Needless to say we will not be returning anytime soon!!!

Went here for dinner with my wife and daughter and couldn't be more disappointed . Ordered my burger med rare and came out very rare. My wife's pasta was so bad she lost her appetite. My daughters mashed potatoes where like a paste that was sitting around all day. Server was ok but never gave us silverware so we got it off another table. Expected to see a manager After pasta was sent back but never saw a manager the whole time we were there. No wonder the restaurant was empty at 6:30.

Ordered the three for all with my girlfriend and when I bit into one of the potato skins I bit into a literal rock. The server was very apologetic and took it off my bill. First time for everything and my teeth are ok. Outside of that it's your typical Friday's atmosphere.

Newly remodeled - new trendy look! A real positive. Still too few fish, healthy vegetable items. I ordered Jack Daniels Salmon with Grilled Shrimp Scampi. Tasty - big complaint shrimp is grilled fully in shell - makes it dry, hard to get to meat.  Also comes with grilled corn bread - yet grill in this case was burnt. To have to convince the waiter who says "it is suppose to come crispy". Maybe so but black and charred is way too crispy.  Also teach a bartender how to make a margarita  Adequate for a cheaper me The above was a few months - there new renovation has lead to them playing loud - very loud - rock music. Hard to carry on a conversation. I was in at 4:30 and when I complained was told "it gets louder at night"  Stay away unless you like loud rock music!! Shame - I use to like this place.

Had their 3/$12.99 deal. Service wasn't so good. Our waitress took forever to bring in our entree. Didn't even check on us to see if everything was okay. But she was quick to bring in our dessert and check. Food and drinks is always good. My daughter loved their chicken fingers with fruit cup. Definitely try their fruit cup as a dessert.
